description: X-Terra Resources Inc., an exploration stage company, engages in the acquisition, exploration, and development of natural resource properties in Canada. It explores for gold, copper, silver, and nickel deposits. The company holds 100% interest in the Troilus East property comprising 182 mining claims that cover an area of 9,300 hectares located in Québec, Canada; and the Ducran property consisting of 70 mining claims located in the Eeyou Istchee/Baie James Territory in the province of Québec. It also holds interest in the Adina lithium project covering an area of approximately 2,018 hectares located in James Bay, Québec; and an option to acquire 70% interest in the Grog and Northwest property located in northeastern New Brunswick, Canada. The company was incorporated in 2013 and is headquartered in Rouyn-Noranda, Canada.
